description:
Probably not a top destination for those visiting Lanzarote, the Temple Hall / Telamon shipwreck is located NE of Arrecife and, it seems, will be removed in 2018 (lucky to have had a chance to capture it!). 
According to wrecksite.eu she was built in Scotland in 1954. On 31-Oct-1981, while on route from the Ivory Coast to Greece, she sustained a water leak and was beached in her current location. 
The wreck sits close to what seems a power station, which at night is lit with yellow floodlights; at the time of shooting there was the “Super Blue Blood Moon”. www.mariolapergola.com
